x4freetext: The ETH polarized-ion source
The gas target is a cylinder 16 mm in diameter.
The entrance and exit windows are 2.5 mum  Havar foils.
For the excitation function at 175-degree a similar gas
cell with 6.5 mum  Havar foil was used. At this angle a
ring detector mounted at 180 degree detected the
deuterons scattered from the target.
The silicon surface barrier detectors
having a sensitive area of 9x38 mm were used.
The detectors are mounted on two plates which can be
rotated independently round the target. On each
turntable there are seven detector positions, 15. degr.
apart. Each table can be adjusted from the outside to
the desired position within 0.1 degr.
In general, four detectors are used on each table
since the electronic equipment has been designed for a
maximum of eight detectors. In this manner four
asymmetries can be measured simultaneously.
